(self.webpackChunkcheatsheet=self.webpackChunkcheatsheet||[]).push([[5048],{8200:(e,n,s)=>{"use strict";s.r(n),s.d(n,{data:()=>a});const a={key:"v-08fc6368",path:"/python/keyword/Finally/",title:"finally",lang:"en-US",frontmatter:{},excerpt:"",headers:[],filePathRelative:"python/keyword/Finally/README.md",git:{updatedTime:162676698e4,contributors:[]}}},8411:(e,n,s)=>{"use strict";s.r(n),s.d(n,{default:()=>t});const a=(0,s(6252).uE)('<h1 id="finally" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#finally" aria-hidden="true">#</a> finally</h1><p>finally is used with try…except block to close up resources or file streams.</p><p>Using finally ensures that the block of code inside it gets executed even if there is an unhandled exception. For example:</p><div class="language-python ext-py line-numbers-mode"><pre class="language-python"><code><span class="token keyword">try</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span>\n    Try<span class="token operator">-</span>block\n<span class="token keyword">except</span> exception1<span class="token punctuation">:</span>\n    Exception1<span class="token operator">-</span>block\n<span class="token keyword">except</span> exception2<span class="token punctuation">:</span>\n    Exception2<span class="token operator">-</span>block\n<span class="token keyword">else</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span>\n    Else<span class="token operator">-</span>block\n<span class="token keyword">finally</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span>\n    Finally<span class="token operator">-</span>block\n</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br></div></div><p>Here if there is an exception in the Try-block, it is handled in the except or else block. But no matter in what order the execution flows, we can rest assured that the Finally-block is executed even if there is an error. This is useful in cleaning up the resources.</p>',5),t={render:function(e,n){return a}}}}]);